en_192153_0	The Nipah virus has lead to 1407 people being put under quarantine in their own homes mainly in Kozhikode and Malappuram districts.
en_192153_1	The Kerala state has witnessed 17 deaths in the last two weeks of whom three people have died in the last two days.
en_192153_2	Rasil, a native of Kozhikode who died on Thursday is suspected to have contracted the virus from Ismail, another Nipah victim.
en_192153_3	Ismail, in turn, is reported to have been infected from Mohammed Sadik, the first suspected Nipah virus victim in Kerala.
en_192153_4	The people who have been placed on house quarantine have been asked by the state government to watch out for symptoms and keep health officers informed.
